import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react'; function MemberDashboard() { const [user] = useState({ full_name: 'John Doe', username: 'johndoe', role: 'Member' }); const [myEvents] = useState([ { id: 1, name: 'Weekly Rehearsal', date: '2024-11-20', time: '18:00', type: 'Rehearsal', location: 'Main Hall' }, { id: 2, name: 'Sunday Service', date: '2024-11-24', time: '10:00', type: 'Performance', location: 'Church Sanctuary' } ]); const [myAttendance] = useState([ { id: 1, event: 'Weekly Rehearsal', date: '2024-11-13', status: 'Present' }, { id: 2, event: 'Sunday Service', date: '2024-11-10', status: 'Present' }, { id: 3, event: 'Weekly Rehearsal', date: '2024-11-06', status: 'Absent' } ]); const calculateAttendanceRate = () => { if (myAttendance.length === 0) return 0; const present = myAttendance.filter(a => a.status === 'Present').length; return Math.round((present / myAttendance.length) * 100); }; return (

Welcome back, {user.full_name}!

Keep up the great work with Nehilot Worship

{calculateAttendanceRate()}%

Your Attendance Rate

{/* Upcoming Events */}
Upcoming Events
{myEvents.map(event => (
{event.name}
{event.date}

Time: {event.time} | Type: {event.type}

{event.location}
))}
{/* My Attendance */}
My Recent Attendance
{myAttendance.map(record => ( ))}
Date Event Status
{record.date} {record.event} {record.status}
); } export default MemberDashboard;
